# .NET Project Rules (Reusable)

## Purpose
These are global rules for DiamondSim. Include these at the top of any feature PRP.

## Environment
- Language: C# 12, .NET 8 (net8.0)
- Test framework: **NUnit** only
- Repo layout:
  - Source: `src/DiamondSim/`
  - Tests: `tests/DiamondSim.Tests/`
- Style guides: follow `.rules/style.md` and `.rules/testing.md`

## Conventions
- Namespaces: file-scoped (`namespace DiamondSim;`)
- Braces: K&R (opening brace on the same line)
- Deterministic tests: always use `SeededRandom(<constant>)`
- Do not change target frameworks or add packages unless asked
- Keep diffs small; do not rename/move existing files without explicit instruction
- Build/test commands:
  - `dotnet restore`
  - `dotnet build`
  - `dotnet test`

## When implementing
- Add tests first (TDD), then code
- Do not weaken or delete existing tests
- Respect `.editorconfig` and `.vscode/settings.json`
